A JMPD officer gets ready for Crowd Control in a violent clash that was anticipated between ANC and DA supporters in the 12 February march. JOHANNESBURG - A Johannesburg Metro Police Department officer has been shot and injured in a robbery in the Johannesburg CBD. Police were responding to an armed robbery at a restaurant. Suspects opened fire, hitting an officer in the leg. READ: 2 police officers allegedly on the run after Rosettenville shootout - IPID He was rushed to the hospital for treatment. The City's Public Safety MMC, David Tembe, has assured residents the CBD will be made safer. Around 2,000 officers have been deployed to the crime-ridden area.